I have successfully implemented all backend files for the comprehensive API Rate Limiting and Throttling System. Here's a summary of what was created:

## Core Rate Limiting Package (`internal/shared/ratelimit/`)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `limiter.go` | Core sliding window rate limiter using Redis sorted sets |
| `config.go` | Rate limit policy configuration structures (Policy, Violation, TrustedClient) |
| `redis.go` | Redis client wrapper for rate limit operations |
| `resolver.go` | Hierarchical policy resolution engine (Global > Org > User > API Key > Endpoint) |
| `middleware.go` | HTTP middleware for rate limit enforcement |
| `burst.go` | Burst vs sustained rate limit implementation |
| `bypass.go` | Trusted client bypass logic |
| `circuit_breaker.go` | Circuit breaker pattern for failing endpoints |
| `queue.go` | Priority request queuing system |
| `metrics.go` | OpenTelemetry metrics for rate limiting |
| `alert.go` | Violation alert notification system |
| `repository.go` | Database repository for policy and violation storage |
| `print_quota.go` | Print-specific quota system extending base quota |

